{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_30","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-exporter-otlp-common:1.20.0`.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7428-fails-java-run-io.opentelemetry-opentelemetry-exporter-otlp-common-1.20.0-56dc76a7\n\nThe original failing stage was the JVM test run: `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-exporter-otlp-common:1.20.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T12-08-25-206678Z.log` shows 2 assertion failures because 1.20.0 now writes numeric JSON values (`\"severityNumber\":13` and `\"kind\":2`) where the old test expected enum names (`\"SEVERITY_NUMBER_WARN\"` and `\"SPAN_KIND_SERVER\"`). The preserved work branch contains that test update, and later reruns are green: `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-exporter-otlp-common:1.20.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T12-11-27-556539Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-exporter-otlp-common:1.20.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-06-06T12-09-38-062810Z.log` both show all 6 tests passing.\n\nThe remaining job failure appears to be metadata/coverage generation, not the fixed Java test. `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-exporter-otlp-common:1.20.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-06-06T12-09-36-129812Z.log` fails during `generateMetadata` with `Could not find agent library native-image-agent ... libnative-image-agent.so: cannot open shared object file`, so `stats/io.opentelemetry/opentelemetry-exporter-otlp-common/1.20.0/stats.json` was never produced. That matches `stats/io.opentelemetry/opentelemetry-exporter-otlp-common/1.20.0/execution-metrics.json`, which records run status `failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file` / `artifacts.metadata_file` as `None`, so dynamic-access coverage is unavailable.\n\nRecommended manual next steps:\n1. Inspect or cherry-pick the passing candidate from the preserved work branch, especially commit `62a51580998e8f9aed24b0d5695725c3a73fe6bf`.\n2. Fix the GraalVM agent environment so `generateMetadata` can load `native-image-agent` (`libnative-image-agent.so`), then rerun metadata/stat generation for `io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-exporter-otlp-common:1.20.0`.\n3. After stats regenerate, rerun the coordinate’s full verification (`test` plus native trace/coverage) to confirm the fix and recover dynamic-access coverage."}}
